=== November 2014 memo by Jeh Johnson ===

On November 20, 2014, a number of announcements were made by the administration of then United States president [[Barack Obama]] surrounding changes to immigration enforcement. The most famous of these announcements was [[Deferred Action for Parents of Americans]]. Two other announcements, both in the form of memos by then [[U.S. Department of Homeland Security]] Secretary [[Jeh Johnson]]:

* One memo announced that the Secure Communities program was discontinued. In particular, ICE was to no longer issue detainers.<ref>{{cite web|url = https://www.dhs.gov/sites/default/files/publications/14_1120_memo_secure_communities.pdf|title = Secure Communities|publisher = [[U.S. Department of Homeland Security]]|last = Johnson|first = Jeh Charles|authorlink = Jeh Johnson|date = November 20, 2014|accessdate = June 20, 2016}}</ref>
* Another memo, titled "Policies for the Apprehension, Detention and Removal of Undocumented Immigrants" provided guidelines for what would later become the Priority Enforcement Program.<ref name=johnson-pep-memo/>

